NULL,NULL,NULL),(3157,'2018-06-13 14:14:08','Wastage in our industry can be attributed in no small part to one issue.  To date businesses have been reluctant to tackle that problem and instead worked around it.  That has stifled progress.\n\n\n\nThe end result of our project will be a novel tool to manage the issue and substantially reduce the wastage caused by it.\n\n',1380,231,148,NULL),(3158,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(3159,'2018-06-13 14:14:08','Three principal risks exist at this stage:\n\n1.        The academic scale up fails to replicate the smaller results either entirely or not to a satisfactory level. In this event the academic partner would begin a controlled scale back to identify if the method needs to be altered during scale up to replicate results.  In the event that the issue can only be identified in the small scale we would build that into our planning for the isolation phase\n\n2.      During the phase to engineer a technique to isolate the issue we anticipate that there are inherent safety issues.  We have consulted an independent firm to ensure that suitable equipment and measures have been put in place to minimise the risk to staff.\n\n3.    Although we are confident that our fabrication partner is the best option for the prototype solution there is an indication that a particular piece of heavy machinery, currently unavailable in the UK will be required.  Our Fabrication partner has already investigated options for accessing this equipment in the Far East and an appropriate budget has been set aside to be used for this purpose if required.\n\n',1409,231,148,NULL),(3160,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(3161,'2018-06-13 14:14:08','The tool will give the consortium the leading edge on the technology as currently no one else is close to considering developing a solution.\n\n\n\nThe Industry will be able to reduce wastage by a significant degree and pass those savings on to the consumer or reinvest into advancing the field.\n\n\n\nInside 2 years it is estimated that a very large sum of money can be recouped by using our solution\n\n',1397,231,148,NULL),(3162,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(3163,'2018-06-13 14:14:08','The project is based on Manchester?s novel IP that, for the first time, allows SLM to be conducted without any need for anchors/supports. A search of the literature has established that the advances proposed in this project on which RAMP are based are not available via any commercially available process. In addition, the development and supply of tailored materials by Empire and a dedicated high temperature rig by Ludlow will involve further, critical degrees of innovation that will help to build a portfolio of IP to enhance commercial exploitation. NB. RAMP does not simply reduce stresses by working at higher temperatures; it involves a novel step based on manufacturing engineering and material science that completely eliminates stresses.',1405,231,148,NULL),(3164,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(3165,'2018-06-13 14:14:08','Within the Industry one issue has caused progress in the field to be stifled.  Up until now any advancement has been made by working around this anomaly.\n\n\n\nWe propose to tackle the situation head on and develop a tool that will circumvent the problem entirely allowing development to advance.\n\n',1385,231,148,NULL),(3166,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(3167,'2018-06-13 14:14:08','The issue affects the entire field, the market value of which is significant, and accounts for a percentage of its annual overhead.  A tool to reduce that amount by a significant proportion would be taken up by the entire industry.\n\n\n\nAt this time no other solutions are available or near market giving us the leading edge on market share.\n\n\n\nManufacture and development could remain in the United Kingdom with an international export market.\n\n',1389,231,148,NULL),(3168,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(3169,'2018-06-13 14:14:08','Our Academic partner has developed a technique to identify 